      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Primary amines react with esters to yield amides: RCO<sub>2</sub>R′ + R″NH<sub>2</sub> → RCONHR″ + R′OH. Propose a mechanism for the following reaction of an <i>α</i>,<i>β</i>-unsaturated ester.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbHdXIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--ed50d440c8314cf2991c3b05f44f59e6b87768d0/OChem_19_EC_041.jpg\" alt=\"The reaction shows an ester with methylamine to form amide and methanol. The amide structure shows a cyclopentanone ring with nitrogen adjacent to the carbonyl, bearing a methyl group.\">",
